Policy.Label: Reservation 'ONLY'
Policy.Description: Ability to make a 'Reservation Only' no ticketing options provided. NOTE: This Policy should not be granted to Corporate Clients.

Policy.Label: Order Manager
Policy.Description: Allows the user to access Bookings Manager

Policy.Label: Fares Option 1 Any fare type in grid
Policy.Description: This option allows the use of any fare type displayed in grid. NOTE: System default requires the cheapest fare to be selected.

Policy.Label: Fares Option 2 Non-cheapest fare taken
Policy.Description: This option requires a reason to be selected when the cheapest fare is not taken. NOTE: Only applies if Fares Option 1 is not enabled.

Policy.Label: First Class allowed
Policy.Description:
Allows First Class to also be booked. (System default is Standard Class only)
NOTE: Overrides all First Class options below if enabled.

Policy.Label: First Class allowed for longer journeys
Policy.Description:
Allows First class to be booked if the journey is more than 60 minutes.
NOTE: Can work in conjunction with First Class options below .

Policy.Label: First Class allowed when below threshold
Policy.Description: Allows First Class to be booked if the fare is less than 0% more than the cheapest fare for the journey. NOTE: Overrides the First Class options below if enabled.

Policy.Label: First Class allowed when it's the cheapest fare
Policy.Description: Allows First Class to be booked when the cheapest fare for the journey is a First Class fare. NOTE: Overrides the First Class option below if enabled

Policy.Label: Open Returns allowed
Policy.Description: Allows Open Returns to also be booked. NOTE: System default is Singles and Returns Only.

Policy.Label: First Class allowed when cheaper than Standard
Policy.Description: Allows First Class to be booked when cheaper than the most expensive Standard Class fare.

Policy.Label: Booker Option 1
Policy.Description: Enables Booking - using the default account set for the user/unit. NOTE: Can be combined with Booker Option 2.

Policy.Label: Booker Option 2
Policy.Description: Enables Booking - using a personal credit card. NOTE: Can be combined with Booker Option 1.

Policy.Label: Allow Additional Travelcards
Policy.Description: Allows additional Travelcards to be added to the order item.

Policy.Label: Display Delivery Note
Policy.Description: Display delivery note address during booking process (delivery note will be addressed to booker if not displayed).

Policy.Label: Delivery Address Mandatory
Policy.Description: Completion of the displayed delivery note address is mandatory.

Policy.Label: Preset Delivery to Booker
Policy.Description: Pre-populate displayed delivery note address with booker's address (default is leave address blank).

Policy.Label: Preset Delivery to Selected Unit
Policy.Description: Pre-populate displayed delivery note address with address of unit selected on Unit Selection page (overrides blank/booker's address if unit selected).

Policy.Label: Delivery Address Not Editable
Policy.Description: User cannot edit pre-populated delivery note address.

Policy.Label: Display Extra Details
Policy.Description: Allow user to enter special requirements/extra details for printing on the delivery note.
